About Me

Creating Common Sense Digital experiences

With nearly 3 years of experience in UI/UX design and frontend development, I craft user-centric digital products that balance visual appeal with functionality. My approach combines intuitive design with thoughtful product architecture to align business goals with a seamless user experience.

While simultaneously serving active duty, I worked with various startup development teams to create innovative digital products across multiple industries including gaming software, clinical healthcare & education, and event services. Following release from the US ARMY, I joined Amazon's Grocery Logistics Team as a Supply Chain Manager while continuing to pursue external design endeavors. I also started a YouTube channel named Bitmute in 2025, creating longform educational content around HTML, CSS, and Javascript front-end development

When I'm not developing, you can find me training for Ironman Triathlons, creating content for my YouTube channel, or spending time with my wife and other people I love.
